The paper deals with lossy compression, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of logarithmic loss as a distortion criterion is a common approach in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the successive refinement problem, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the results to discrete memoryless sources suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the concept of universality is relevant to many areas of computer science, including systems and information theory (cs.SI).
